# Interpolation guard for the e2e stack — intentionally contains no values.
#
# `make e2e` passes this file via `docker compose --env-file docker/e2e.env`
# when it creates the e2e-app and e2e-artifact-host containers, replacing the
# default `.env` lookup. Without it, Docker Compose would interpolate every
# `${VAR:-default}` in docker-compose.yml from the developer's personal .env,
# quietly leaking local settings (SESSION_*, TRUSTED_PROXIES, REVERB_*, ...)
# into the supposedly isolated e2e services and making browser tests behave
# differently per machine.
#
# With this file, interpolation resolves purely from the compose-file defaults
# plus the E2E_* variables the Makefile exports explicitly.
#
# Keep this file comments-only: E2eIsolationConfigurationTest fails the build
# if any assignment appears here.
